    • Method Detail

      • getEngineer

        Engineer getEngineer()
        Returns the value of the 'Engineer' reference. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Designations'. Engineer whose capacity is allocated to work on the containing [engineered element](EngineeredElement.html).
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Engineer' reference.
        See Also:
        setEngineer(Engineer), EngineeringPackage.getAllocation_Engineer(), Engineer.getDesignations()

      • getCategory

        IssueCategory getCategory()
        Returns the value of the 'Category' reference. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Allocations'. Optional issue category for this allocation. E.g. a allocation can be made to "Documentation" or "Test coverage" categories.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Category' reference.
        See Also:
        setCategory(IssueCategory), EngineeringPackage.getAllocation_Category(), IssueCategory.getAllocations()
